wikipedia_page.main: Terence Murphy (born 14 January 1940) is an English former professional footballer who played in the Football League as a left half for Crewe Alexandra. He played non-league football for Northwich Victoria and Witton Albion, managed clubs including Rhyl, Runcorn, Altrincham and Witton Albion, and acted as scout for the latter club.
